[{"id":"VR708807","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two concentric pulleys of different radii wrapped with a string each. The larger pulley has a radius of 0.2 meter and a force of 4 newtons pulls downward on the string hanging off its right side. The smaller pulley has a radius of 0.1 meter; a force of 10 newtons pulls downward on the string that hangs off its left side, and another force of 4 newtons pulls downward on the string that hangs off its right side.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR708807.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two pulleys of different radii are rigidly attached together at their centers, as shown in the figure. The smaller pulley, of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.1 meter\"><math alttext=\"0.1 meter\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.1</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></span></span>, has a lightweight string wrapped around it. A force of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 newtons\"><math alttext=\"10 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>10</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></span></span> pulls downward on the left section of string, and a force of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 newtons\"><math alttext=\"4 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></span></span> pulls downward on the right section of string. The larger pulley, of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.2 meter\"><math alttext=\"0.2 meter\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.2</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></span></span>, also has a lightweight string wrapped around it. A single force of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 newtons\"><math alttext=\"4 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></span></span> pulls downward on this string. Which of the following gives the correct direction of the two-pulley systemâ€™s angular acceleration, and provides appropriate supporting evidence?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR708807_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Clockwise. The sum of the torques from the two <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 newtons\"><math alttext=\"4 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></span></span> forces is greater than torque from the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 newtons\"><math alttext=\"10 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>10</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></span></span> force.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Clockwise. The sum of the lever arms for the two <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 newtons\"><math alttext=\"4 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></span></span> forces is greater than the lever arm for the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 newtons\"><math alttext=\"10 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>10</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></span></span> force.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Counterclockwise. The torque from the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 newtons\"><math alttext=\"10 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>10</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></span></span> force is greater than each of the torques from the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 newtons\"><math alttext=\"4 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></span></span> forces.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Counterclockwise. The <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 newtons\"><math alttext=\"10 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>10</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></span></span> force is greater than the sum of the two <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 newtons\"><math alttext=\"4 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></span></span> forces.</p>"],"answer":0}]